Durban - A man and his wife have been hospitalised after being shot in New Germany, Pinetown on Sunday. The shooting incident took place on Reading Avenue in Berkshire Downs, New Germany. Shawn Herbst, a spokesperson for Netcare 911 paramedics, said that the husband and wife team operate a videography business. Both of them were sitting in their car when another car with three unknown occupants approached them. "They were at a client's house to continue filming a wedding when the car pulled up. The occupants inside the car shot them. The husband who is believed to be in his fifties sustained moderate injuries when he was shot in his right arm. The wife also in her fifties sustained serious injuries when she was shot in the abdomen," Herbst said. The woman had to be airlifted to hospital in a critical condition. Pinetown police are investigating a case of attempted murder. Daily News 